Package com.poesys.db.dao.insert

Interface Summary
IInsert<T extends IDbDto> An interface for a Command pattern class that inserts an object or link into the database based on values in a data transfer object (DTO).
IInsertBatch<T extends IDbDto> An interface for a Command pattern class that inserts a collection of objects into the database in batches with a specified batch size.
IInsertCollection<T extends IDbDto> An interface for a Command pattern class that inserts a collection of objects into the database in one group.
IInsertSql<T extends IDbDto> An interface that defines the set of operations required by an IInsert or IInsertBatch object to build a SQL INSERT statement for a data transfer object (DTO).
 

Class Summary
Insert<T extends IDbDto> An implementation of the IInsert generic interface that contains the base code for inserting a single object into the database.
InsertBatch<T extends IDbDto> An implementation of the IInsertBatch generic interface that contains the base code for inserting a batch of objects into the database.
InsertCache<T extends IDbDto> A subclass of Insert that caches the inserted object.
InsertCacheBatch<T extends IDbDto> A subclass of the InsertBatch class that adds all the inserted objects to a cache after inserting them.
InsertCacheCollection<T extends IDbDto> A subclass of the InsertCollection class that adds the collection of objects to a cache after inserting them in the database.
InsertCacheFactory<T extends IDbDto,C extends Collection<T>> The InsertCacheFactory lets you generate an insert object appropriate to your desired insert framework.
InsertCacheNoKey<T extends IDbDto> A subclass of InsertNoKey that caches the inserted object after key generation.
InsertCacheNoKeyCollection<T extends IDbDto> A subclass of InsertNoKeyCollection that caches the object after key generation
InsertCollection<T extends IDbDto> An implementation of the IInsertCollection generic interface that contains the base code for inserting a collection of objects into the database.
InsertFactory<T extends IDbDto> The InsertFactory lets you generate an insert object appropriate to your desired insert framework.
InsertMemcached<T extends IDbDto> A subclass of Insert that caches the inserted object using memcached.
InsertMemcachedBatch<T extends IDbDto> A subclass of the InsertBatch class that adds all the inserted objects to a memcached cache after inserting them.
InsertMemcachedCollection<T extends IDbDto> A subclass of the InsertCollection class that adds the collection of objects to a memcached cache after inserting them in the database.
InsertMemcachedNoKey<T extends IDbDto> A subclass of InsertNoKey that caches the inserted object in a memcached cache after key generation.
InsertMemcachedNoKeyCollection<T extends IDbDto> A subclass of InsertNoKeyCollection that caches the object after key generation
InsertNoKey<T extends IDbDto> An interface for a Command pattern class that inserts an object into the database based on values in a data transfer object (DTO).
InsertNoKeyCollection<T extends IDbDto> An implementation of the IInsertCollection generic interface that contains the base code for inserting a collection of objects that do not contain primary key values (identity or auto-generated keys) into the database.
